    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Computer Associates Promotes Kumar to C.E.O.</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">Compiled by Warren Strugatch</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Strugatch, Warren</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Computer Associates International promotes president Sanjay Kumar to chief executive, succeeding Charles Wang, who remains chairman (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Computer Associates International (NYSE: CA) promoted its president, Sanjay Kumar, to the post of chief executive, succeeding Charles Wang, who remains chairman. The promotion of Mr. Kumar, 38, who is also the chief operating officer, will allow Mr. Wang to concentrate on spinning off the company's technology into new companies.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Computer Associates International (NYSE: CA) promoted its president, Sanjay Kumar, to the post of chief executive, succeeding Charles Wang, who remains chairman. The promotion of Mr. Kumar, 38, who is also the chief operating officer, will allow Mr. Wang to concentrate on spinning off the company's technology into new companies.</p>
        <p>The move, which had been expected, had little immediate effect on the stock price, which has tumbled from its late June high of $50.</p>
